<!-- ── macOS ─────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<div class="tab-pane fade show active" id="pane-mac" role="tabpanel">

```bash
# Install Homebrew (if not already installed)
/bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"

# Install prerequisites
brew install git ruby docker

# Or run the automated setup script
curl -fsSL {{RAW_GITHUB_URL}}/scripts/platform/setup-macos.sh | bash
```

</div>

<!-- ── Linux ─────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<div class="tab-pane fade" id="pane-linux" role="tabpanel">

```bash
# Debian / Ubuntu
sudo apt update && sudo apt install -y git ruby-full docker.io docker-compose

# Fedora / RHEL
sudo dnf install -y git ruby docker docker-compose

# Or run the automated setup script
curl -fsSL {{RAW_GITHUB_URL}}/scripts/platform/setup-linux.sh | bash
```

</div>

<!-- ── Windows (WSL) ─────────────────────────────────────── -->
<div class="tab-pane fade" id="pane-wsl" role="tabpanel">

> **Note:** Zer0-Mistakes works on Windows through WSL 2 (Windows Subsystem for Linux).

```powershell
# Install WSL 2 from PowerShell (Admin)
wsl --install -d Ubuntu
```

After WSL is set up, open your Ubuntu terminal and run:

```bash
# Inside WSL
curl -fsSL {{RAW_GITHUB_URL}}/scripts/platform/setup-wsl.sh | bash
```

Make sure **Docker Desktop** → Settings → Resources → WSL Integration is enabled for your distro.

</div>

<!-- ── GitHub Fork ───────────────────────────────────────── -->
<div class="tab-pane fade" id="pane-gh" role="tabpanel">

Fork the theme directly on GitHub — no local tools required for setup:

```bash
# Using GitHub CLI (recommended)
gh repo fork {{GITHUB_REPO}} --clone --remote
cd {{REPOSITORY_NAME}}

# Or click "Fork" on https://github.com/{{GITHUB_REPO}}
```

Then run the post-fork install:

```bash
./install.sh --fork
```

</div>
</div>

