## 2. Get the Theme

```bash
# Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/{{GITHUB_REPO}}.git
cd {{REPOSITORY_NAME}}
```

## 3. Start Development Server

### Using Docker (Recommended)

```bash
docker-compose up
```

Your site will be available at **{{DEFAULT_URL}}**

### Using Local Ruby

```bash
bundle install
bundle exec jekyll serve --config _config.yml,_config_dev.yml
```

---

## 4. Customize Your Site

Edit `_config.yml` to personalize your site — or use the **[Setup Wizard](/setup/)** to generate configuration interactively.

```yaml
title: Your Site Title
description: Your site description
founder: Your Name
url: https://your-username.github.io
```

## 5. Add Content

| Content Type | Location | Example Filename |
|---|---|---|
| Blog posts | `pages/_posts/` | `2025-01-27-my-first-post.md` |
| Documentation | `pages/_docs/` | `getting-started.md` |
| Static pages | `pages/` | `about.md` |

## 6. Deploy to GitHub Pages

```bash
git add -A
git commit -m "feat: initial site setup"
git push origin main
```

Your site will deploy automatically at `https://<username>.github.io/<repo>/`.

